Bad Design 1: No Tables and Chairs in Front of KC Foods

Description:
The food outlet does not provide tables or chairs for customers to sit and eat. Customers are forced to stand or leave immediately after purchasing food, reducing comfort and convenience.

Source of Photograph: (CAPTURED PICTURE)

Place:
KC Foods – Campus Food Court

Reasons why the design is bad:

No seating arrangement for customers.

Causes discomfort while eating.

Crowding occurs during peak hours.

Not suitable for elderly people or students carrying bags.

Reduces the overall customer experience.


Suggested Improvement:

Provide sufficient tables and chairs.

Arrange seating to avoid congestion.

Include accessible seating for all users.

Maintain cleanliness around the seating area.



