Bad Design 2: Menu Board is Not Clearly Visible

Description:
The menu board is placed in a location where customers cannot easily read it. The text is too small or positioned too high, making it difficult to view the available food items and prices.

Source of Photograph: (CAPTURED PICTURE)

Place:
KC Foods – Order Counter

Reasons why the design is bad:

Menu is difficult to read from a distance.

Small font size reduces readability.

Customers spend more time deciding.

Creates longer waiting queues.

First-time visitors may become confused.


Suggested Improvement:

Install a larger menu board.

Use bigger fonts with high-contrast colors.

Position the menu at eye level.

Display digital menus or multiple menu boards.



