Bad Design 3: Switch Board Without Labels

Description:
The switches are not labeled, making it difficult for users to identify which switch controls which appliance or light. Users often need to try multiple switches before finding the correct one.

Source of Photograph: (CAPTURED PICTURE)

Place:
Classroom / Laboratory / Office

Reasons why the design is bad:

No indication of switch functions.

Users waste time searching for the correct switch.

Can lead to accidental operation of equipment.

Difficult for new users and visitors.

Poor usability and organization.


Suggested Improvement:

Label each switch clearly.

Use printed stickers or engraved labels.

Group related switches together.

Add indicator lights where necessary.

Maintain a consistent switch arrangement.


